<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Crystalmyst</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-07-20 19:02:30</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>In response to Speel's comment earlier that the Amice is the only Loam piece clearly worth getting:<BR>
<BR>
How can you possibly arrive at this conclusion?  Let's evaluate for a moment.  Obviously the most important stat for all pure casters is INT.  However.. the second most important stat is clearly AGI (except for Enchanters which need CHA).<BR>
AGI is the stat that inherently increases your AC and improves the effectiveness of your defensive skills (Dodge, Defense, etc.)  Virtually all of the Loam armor pieces give major bonuses to AGI, as well as decent bonuses to INT, and even more importantly mana.<BR>
Not to mention the huge bonuses you get to CHA for most of the pieces, which makes them even more beneficial to Enchanters.  After checking the stats on this armor and comparing it to other available pieces, I have come up with the following:<BR>
<BR>
The Amice, and Leggings are clearly the best available period for pure casters. (and this includes all planes gear.. etc)<BR>
The Arms are the best available except for planes gear.<BR>
The Cloak is best available for Enchanters, and probably the second best for all other casters (after the quested Mystic cloak).<BR>
The Shoes are arguably best available for enchanters, and probably second only to cryosilk (planes shoes), and GE boots for the other classes.<BR>
The Cap is second only to planes gear for enchanters, and second to planes gear and the runed cowl for the other classes.<BR>
The veil granted is sub par at best.. there are much better veils.  And the bracers are only fairly useful to enchanters (although golden chitten is likely still better even for them).<BR>
<BR>
Clearly, this armor kicks butt and should demand very high premiums in trade and sale for those that can't use it.</font></td></tr></table>
