<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Crystalmyst</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-07-28 23:12:42</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Just a quick comparison here for everyone:<BR>
<BR>
"Legs, bah who needs legs, I have silversilk", "by the time you could get them you'll be able to get Cryosilk on the planes which is better."<BR>
<BR>
Let's see here.. Cryosilk legs -- Don't Exist!<BR>
There are 4 different pairs of leggings available on the planes, one for each caster class.  The stats and names follow:<BR>
<BR>
Magician - Apothic Kilt - ac 5 / 5 str / 10 sv cold / 25 hps<BR>
Necro - Blighted Trousers - ac 5 / 3 str / 4 dex / 10 sv cold / 10 hps<BR>
Enchanter - Insideous Pantaloons - ac 5 / 3 str / 3 cha / 10 sv cold / 15 hps<BR>
Wizard - Carmine Pants - ac 5 / 3 str / 3 sta / 10 sv cold / 15 hps<BR>
<BR>
and the already mentioned Silversilk.. probably the only other piece worth mentioning<BR>
ac 4 / 4 agi / 12 hps<BR>
<BR>
Now then, we have Loam Encrusted Pantaloons:<BR>
ac 5 / 8 agi / 3 int / 10 sv disease / 10 hps / 5 mana<BR>
<BR>
I think it's pretty obvious here which is best.. by a long shot.  Even considering what's available on the planes.<BR>
<BR>
Granted, wheather or not they are worth paying for I guess all depends on individual preference and available resourses.  But that doesn't change the fact that Loam is the best.</font></td></tr></table>
